50|$|In July 2014, Paddy Power was criticised by the <b>Information</b> <b>Commissioner's</b> Office for its {{response}} to an incident in 2010, where a hacker was able to obtain personal information of more than 649,000 people from its website. The data included addresses, email addresses, phone numbers, dates of birth and security questions and answers. Paddy Power did not inform the <b>Information</b> <b>Commissioner's</b> Office until four years later.|$|R
