25|$|On Friday 27 April 2007 the High Court {{rejected}} Mr Steven Sugar's {{challenge to}} the <b>Information</b> <b>Commissioner's</b> decision. However, on 11 February 2009 the House of Lords (the UK's highest court) reinstated the Information Tribunal's decision to allow Mr Sugar's appeal against the <b>Information</b> <b>Commissioner's</b> decision. The matter {{goes back to the}} High Court for determination of the BBC's further appeal on a point of law against the Tribunal's decision.|$|R
